00:03:44.600 --> 00:03:49.250
When I was nine, the Cultural
Revolution broke out.

00:03:49.250 --> 00:03:52.010
And I often studied
by myself at home,

00:03:52.010 --> 00:03:55.190
because there was not
much to learn at school.

00:03:55.190 --> 00:04:01.490
And like many Chinese youth,
I was sent to the countryside

00:04:01.490 --> 00:04:02.990
after high school.

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:07.340
And I would continue to study
after a day's hard work,

00:04:07.340 --> 00:04:09.640
hard labor.

00:04:09.640 --> 00:04:11.890
And after the end of
the Cultural Revolution,

00:04:11.890 --> 00:04:15.910
I entered the Peking University
and spent nine years there,

00:04:15.910 --> 00:04:21.220
where I met and married
my fellow graduate student

00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:25.600
and got my PhD in physics.

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:29.170
We came to the
United States in 1989

00:04:29.170 --> 00:04:33.130
for better career opportunity
and a better life.

00:04:33.130 --> 00:04:40.580
And in 1995, we
joined Penn State.

00:04:40.580 --> 00:04:48.340
And so after many years
and two daughters,

00:04:48.340 --> 00:04:53.560
and here you see
Joyce and Sarah,

00:04:53.560 --> 00:04:59.620
we realized that our home is
here and our careers are here.

00:04:59.620 --> 00:05:03.490
So we decided to
become US citizens.

00:05:03.490 --> 00:05:07.030
In 2009, I moved to
Temple University,

00:05:07.030 --> 00:05:10.260
and built my
research group there.

00:05:10.260 --> 00:05:14.320
Just to give you some idea
about the research I'm doing,

00:05:14.320 --> 00:05:16.830
here are some of the
most important papers

00:05:16.830 --> 00:05:20.640
I have published over
a period of 30 years.

00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:27.970
It's about thin films, about
100 thousands of an inch thick.

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:31.830
And I have studied a
wide range of materials

00:05:31.830 --> 00:05:34.890
from superconductors, to
ferroelectrics, from borides,

00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:36.750
to oxides.

00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:40.650
America has given
me the opportunity

00:05:40.650 --> 00:05:46.800
to a level in my profession that
I would not have imagined when

00:05:46.800 --> 00:05:48.030
I was a youngster in China.

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:57.590
And so May, 2015, is
a normal, busy day

00:05:57.590 --> 00:06:02.360
for me filled with
my work, my teaching,

00:06:02.360 --> 00:06:06.830
and my administrative duty
as chair of the physics

00:06:06.830 --> 00:06:08.360
department.

00:06:08.360 --> 00:06:14.000
And Joyce just came back
home a day later from college

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:17.570
for a few days, and
Sarah was anxious

00:06:17.570 --> 00:06:21.870
about her dental
surgery the next day.

00:06:21.870 --> 00:06:27.100
And I gave a public lecture
at a science festival

00:06:27.100 --> 00:06:31.070
called the Pint of
Science at dinnertime,

00:06:31.070 --> 00:06:33.040
and then I went to the
Philadelphia Airport

00:06:33.040 --> 00:06:36.970
to pick up my wife, who came
back from a oversee conference

00:06:36.970 --> 00:06:38.490
trip.

00:06:38.490 --> 00:06:43.860
And by the time we made
a plan that we will all

00:06:43.860 --> 00:06:47.910
visit a famous Korean
restaurant for fried chicken,

00:06:47.910 --> 00:06:53.180
it was already
way past midnight.

00:06:53.180 --> 00:06:57.410
A few hours later,
our life would

00:06:57.410 --> 00:07:01.730
be suddenly and forever
changed when I was woken up

00:07:01.730 --> 00:07:04.850
by loud knocks on my door.

00:07:04.850 --> 00:07:09.840
It was May 21st, 2015, before
7 o'clock in the morning.

00:07:12.470 --> 00:07:16.760
The pounding on the door were
so loud and urgent that I

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:21.170
ran to open the door
without even fully dressed.

00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:24.080
And I saw many people
outside my house.

00:07:24.080 --> 00:07:28.370
Some were armed, and some
had the battering ram

00:07:28.370 --> 00:07:31.390
ready to take down my door.

00:07:31.390 --> 00:07:35.000
And after an agent showed
me his badge, asked my name,

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:36.800
and announced my arrest.

00:07:36.800 --> 00:07:41.630
And another agent turned me
around and put handcuffs on me.

00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:45.860
And I was in total
shock, and thought,

00:07:45.860 --> 00:07:47.510
there must be a mistake.

00:07:47.510 --> 00:07:50.510
It must be a mistaken identity.

00:07:50.510 --> 00:07:53.510
So I asked them for
what I was arrested,

00:07:53.510 --> 00:07:56.260
and they wouldn't tell me.

00:07:56.260 --> 00:08:01.470
And in the meantime, the armed
agent in bulletproof vest

00:08:01.470 --> 00:08:07.170
burst into my house, running
about, and rounding up

00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:09.350
my wife and the two daughters.

00:08:09.350 --> 00:08:13.430
And one by one, they
came out of their bedroom

00:08:13.430 --> 00:08:16.950
at gunpoint, with
their hands raised.

00:08:16.950 --> 00:08:19.350
And I was really worried
that how frightening this

00:08:19.350 --> 00:08:23.460
must be to them, but I could
not have a word with them.

00:08:23.460 --> 00:08:25.950
And later, I
learned from my wife

00:08:25.950 --> 00:08:29.790
that her top
thought at that time

00:08:29.790 --> 00:08:33.360
was to protect the
12-year-old, Sarah,

00:08:33.360 --> 00:08:36.830
from possible mental damages.

00:08:36.830 --> 00:08:40.565
So the FBI agent let
me put on a shirt

00:08:40.565 --> 00:08:45.160
and let me out of my house
in front of my family.

00:08:45.160 --> 00:08:49.760
And I had no idea when I would
be able to see them again.

00:08:49.760 --> 00:08:52.970
Because in the Cultural
Revolution in China,

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:55.970
it was not unusual for
people to be taken away

00:08:55.970 --> 00:08:59.814
and could not see their
family for a long time.

00:08:59.814 --> 00:09:03.480
So at FBI field office
in Philadelphia,

00:09:03.480 --> 00:09:08.100
I was subjected to
fingerprinting, mug shots,

00:09:08.100 --> 00:09:10.470
and interrogation.

00:09:10.470 --> 00:09:15.480
And when I was transferred
to the US Marshals Service

00:09:15.480 --> 00:09:17.910
to wait for my first
court appearance,

00:09:17.910 --> 00:09:22.410
I was ordered to strip naked,
bend over against the wall

00:09:22.410 --> 00:09:24.630
so that a US Marshal
could check whether I

00:09:24.630 --> 00:09:27.820
hid anything in my body.

00:09:27.820 --> 00:09:31.740
I was in handcuffs all
the time, except when

00:09:31.740 --> 00:09:36.480
I was using a restroom
or locked up in a cell.

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:41.310
During the two-hour
interrogation,

00:09:41.310 --> 00:09:47.670
I was handcuffed to the
table that I was sitting at.

00:09:47.670 --> 00:09:52.170
At the end of the interrogation,
the FBI agent finally

00:09:52.170 --> 00:09:56.520
told me that I was charged
for having made a pocket

00:09:56.520 --> 00:09:59.070
heater, a device
that was covered

00:09:59.070 --> 00:10:03.840
by a non-disclosure agreement
with a Chinese company

00:10:03.840 --> 00:10:07.030
with a Chinese collaborator.

00:10:07.030 --> 00:10:12.100
And I said immediately,
that's absurd.

00:10:12.100 --> 00:10:15.880
The fact is that I had never
shared the pocket heater

00:10:15.880 --> 00:10:19.180
information with
anybody in China.

00:10:19.180 --> 00:10:24.850
And I was shocked,
and think that,

00:10:24.850 --> 00:10:26.980
how could the government
do this to me?

00:10:26.980 --> 00:10:29.980
They charged me for crimes,
and they used these tactics

00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:34.030
for violent criminals
to me and to my family

00:10:34.030 --> 00:10:37.640
without a thread of truth
in their accusation.

00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:39.340
So I was really shocked.

00:10:39.340 --> 00:10:45.160
And to that, the FBI
agent said, Xiaoxing Xi,

00:10:45.160 --> 00:10:50.390
I'm sure the whole thing
today has been surprising.

00:10:50.390 --> 00:10:55.370
And in the afternoon at
my first court appearance,

00:10:55.370 --> 00:11:01.040
I was released on bail
for $100,000 or my house,

00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:05.330
with various travel
restrictions.

00:11:05.330 --> 00:11:08.390
So when I finally
United with Joyce

00:11:08.390 --> 00:11:14.060
and my wife outside of the
jail, it was drizzling.

00:11:16.690 --> 00:11:21.990
And I shivered, because I had
very little clothes on me.

00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:27.720
When we were just pulling
into our driveway, and then

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:33.300
we saw the FBI agent waiting
for us with a search warrant.

00:11:33.300 --> 00:11:36.480
For the next two
hours, the FBI agents

00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:38.970
searched every
corner of our house

00:11:38.970 --> 00:11:43.050
and carried away our belongings.

00:11:43.050 --> 00:11:48.340
When all these were over,
I told Joyce and Sarah

00:11:48.340 --> 00:11:51.160
that dad has done
nothing wrong, but you

00:11:51.160 --> 00:11:57.930
have to prepare for a very,
very hard life ahead of us.

00:11:57.930 --> 00:12:03.860
The charges against me was
about a device called the pocket

00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:05.630
heater.

00:12:05.630 --> 00:12:13.170
And that was developed
by a US company STI.

00:12:13.170 --> 00:12:18.010
And in 2002 to 2003, I
took a sabbatical leave

00:12:18.010 --> 00:12:23.390
from Penn State to work at
Stanford and a Sunnyvale,

00:12:23.390 --> 00:12:28.190
California company called
Conductus near here.

00:12:28.190 --> 00:12:32.570
And in the indictment,
the government

00:12:32.570 --> 00:12:39.040
said that the individual
at this US company

00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:43.360
invented a piece of
technology, a device

00:12:43.360 --> 00:12:48.280
which revolutionized the field
of superconducting magnesium

00:12:48.280 --> 00:12:52.250
diboride thin film growth.

00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:59.280
And this tale of an invention
of a revolutionary device by STI

00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:01.800
was pure fabrication.

00:13:01.800 --> 00:13:06.480
The pocket heater was
invented by a German company

00:13:06.480 --> 00:13:08.290
in the 1990s.

00:13:08.290 --> 00:13:14.460
And STI just modified
it for its own purpose.

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:21.370
And this slide shows
the pocket heater

00:13:21.370 --> 00:13:24.570
that was invented
by Professor Helmut

00:13:24.570 --> 00:13:28.350
Kinder in [INAUDIBLE] Munich.

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:32.070
And a heater is what we use
to heat a substrate when

00:13:32.070 --> 00:13:34.290
we make thin film materials.

00:13:34.290 --> 00:13:39.090
It's much like using
a stove for cooking.

00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:43.170
And the picture that
I'm showing here

00:13:43.170 --> 00:13:51.390
was from his paper published in
1993, and also from the patent

00:13:51.390 --> 00:13:58.990
that the Kinder's company filed,
which was published in 1998.

00:13:58.990 --> 00:14:01.650
And so a pocket heater,
you can see from the left

00:14:01.650 --> 00:14:07.840
that it looks like a cookie can
with half of his cap removed.

00:14:07.840 --> 00:14:15.250
And inside of the pocket,
it was filled with oxygen.

00:14:15.250 --> 00:14:19.340
And there is a
rotating [INAUDIBLE]

00:14:19.340 --> 00:14:25.110
that switched the substrate
on it from the opening where

00:14:25.110 --> 00:14:28.080
metals are deposited
on a substrate

00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:33.000
into the pocket, where
they will be oxidized.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:39.060
And this is a
wide-known invention.

00:14:39.060 --> 00:14:43.670
In the community, it was
known as a Kinder heater.

00:14:43.670 --> 00:14:48.890
In the 1990s, conductors
adopted the Kinder heater

00:14:48.890 --> 00:14:51.310
for their own thin
film production.

00:14:51.310 --> 00:14:56.180
And after conductors and STI
merged at the end of 2002,

00:14:56.180 --> 00:15:00.200
STI continued to use the
Kinder heater for its thin film

00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:02.840
production.

00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:07.620
And this slides shows the STI
pocket heater for magnesium

00:15:07.620 --> 00:15:09.770
diboride thin films.

00:15:09.770 --> 00:15:13.700
And I can toggle it back
and forth like this.

00:15:13.700 --> 00:15:19.610
And the STI pocket heater
looks like a Kinder heater

00:15:19.610 --> 00:15:23.030
and it works like
a Kinder heater.

00:15:23.030 --> 00:15:26.510
STI simply modified
a pocket heater

00:15:26.510 --> 00:15:30.410
so that in the pocket
instead of oxygen,

00:15:30.410 --> 00:15:33.450
now its magnesium vapor.

00:15:33.450 --> 00:15:39.405
And this heater, the STI
started to talk about it

00:15:39.405 --> 00:15:42.900
at conferences from 2003.

00:15:42.900 --> 00:15:48.370
And they published a
paper about it in 2006.

00:15:48.370 --> 00:15:54.080
So the pocket heater is not
classified, it's not sensitive,

00:15:54.080 --> 00:15:58.850
but rather, it's
widely known publicly.

00:15:58.850 --> 00:16:03.910
And the STI I pocket
heater produced

00:16:03.910 --> 00:16:09.870
magnesium diboride thin
films inferior in quality

00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:14.010
compared to the films
produced by the technique

00:16:14.010 --> 00:16:17.250
that I invented at
Penn State before I

00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:19.560
started my sabbatical leave.

00:16:19.560 --> 00:16:23.610
And my technique has been
universally recognized

00:16:23.610 --> 00:16:28.800
as the best technique
for magnesium diboride.

00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:36.060
So in addition, I'm not
aware of any economic value

00:16:36.060 --> 00:16:39.810
of this pocket heater
to the US company.

00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:45.180
And the prosecutor admitted
that the so-called crime

00:16:45.180 --> 00:16:50.550
that committed had no
economic damage to STI.

00:16:50.550 --> 00:16:56.400
So I really don't understand why
the US government should even

00:16:56.400 --> 00:16:58.320
care about a pocket heater.

00:17:02.300 --> 00:17:05.280
So in the indictment,
the government

00:17:05.280 --> 00:17:10.170
alleged that I repeatedly
reproduced, sold, transferred,

00:17:10.170 --> 00:17:13.050
distributed, and otherwise
shared the pocket

00:17:13.050 --> 00:17:16.050
heater and the pocket
heater technology,

00:17:16.050 --> 00:17:20.170
and exploited it for the
benefit of third party in China,

00:17:20.170 --> 00:17:23.400
including government
entities in an effort

00:17:23.400 --> 00:17:27.480
to help Chinese entities become
world leader in the field

00:17:27.480 --> 00:17:30.260
of superconductivity.

00:17:30.260 --> 00:17:33.090
I have never done
any of the things

00:17:33.090 --> 00:17:35.960
that the government
accused me of doing.

00:17:35.960 --> 00:17:39.620
It is utterly
ridiculous that I would

00:17:39.620 --> 00:17:44.510
steal a publicly available
STI pocket heater, which

00:17:44.510 --> 00:17:50.150
is inferior to my own
technique, and that

00:17:50.150 --> 00:17:53.900
somehow could make
the Chinese world

00:17:53.900 --> 00:17:55.790
leaders in superconductivity.

00:17:59.290 --> 00:18:03.540
So there were four
counts in the indictment,

00:18:03.540 --> 00:18:07.620
based on four emails that I
sent from my Temple University

00:18:07.620 --> 00:18:10.350
address to colleagues in China.

00:18:10.350 --> 00:18:15.450
And none of the emails talked
about the pocket heater.

