Once I was prosecuted
despite being innocent,

00:37:16.420 --> 00:37:21.050
our peace of mind
is gone forever.

00:37:21.050 --> 00:37:26.230
So even now, we are living
under a constant concern

00:37:26.230 --> 00:37:29.350
that the government is
still reading my emails,

00:37:29.350 --> 00:37:31.075
listening to my phone calls.

00:37:31.075 --> 00:37:34.120
That anything I say
in the right could

00:37:34.120 --> 00:37:39.190
be twisted by the government
as a reason to charge me.

00:37:39.190 --> 00:37:46.240
Just like a Chinese saying,
to pick bones out of an egg.

00:37:46.240 --> 00:37:50.860
So the question is,
did the government

00:37:50.860 --> 00:37:57.070
target me because my
Chinese ethnic origin?

00:37:57.070 --> 00:38:03.040
And is it because of my visit
to China, to my aging mother,

00:38:03.040 --> 00:38:05.800
my friends, my relatives?

00:38:05.800 --> 00:38:10.360
So my lawyer, Peter
Zeidenberg said,

00:38:10.360 --> 00:38:14.110
if he was Canadian American,
or French American,

00:38:14.110 --> 00:38:17.560
or he was from the UK,
would this have ever gotten

00:38:17.560 --> 00:38:18.970
on the government's radar?

00:38:18.970 --> 00:38:21.840
I don't believe so.

00:38:21.840 --> 00:38:25.410
And when I met my local
counsel, Mike Schwartz,

00:38:25.410 --> 00:38:26.940
for the first time
and I told him

00:38:26.940 --> 00:38:29.940
that I didn't do anything
that the government charged me

00:38:29.940 --> 00:38:34.080
of doing, he asked me,
have you made money

00:38:34.080 --> 00:38:37.770
from your collaboration
with Chinese colleagues?

00:38:37.770 --> 00:38:39.350
And I said no.

00:38:39.350 --> 00:38:43.710
And he then said, it must be
because you are from China.

00:38:46.300 --> 00:38:51.480
So what is alarming
is that my case is not

00:38:51.480 --> 00:38:54.360
the only such cases.

00:38:54.360 --> 00:38:57.950
There was the National
Weather Service hydrologist,

00:38:57.950 --> 00:38:59.590
Sherry Chen.

00:38:59.590 --> 00:39:04.980
And there was Guoqing Cao
and Shuyu Li, the Eli Lilly

00:39:04.980 --> 00:39:06.580
scientists.

00:39:06.580 --> 00:39:11.820
There is a pattern that the
scientist of Chinese origin

00:39:11.820 --> 00:39:17.250
are being charged, and
just for it to be dropped

00:39:17.250 --> 00:39:21.270
later on, without explanation.

00:39:21.270 --> 00:39:25.590
And so this has prompted
many people like members

00:39:25.590 --> 00:39:30.390
of the Congress, the US
commission on civil rights,

00:39:30.390 --> 00:39:34.710
and many civil
rights organizations,

00:39:34.710 --> 00:39:38.550
to ask the Department of
Justice to investigate

00:39:38.550 --> 00:39:42.840
whether race, and ethnicity,
and national origin

00:39:42.840 --> 00:39:47.060
had anything to do with
these kind of false charges.

00:39:51.220 --> 00:39:55.120
So one point I want to say
is that the racial profiling

00:39:55.120 --> 00:39:58.810
is not just a Chinese
American issue,

00:39:58.810 --> 00:40:01.420
but an issue for all Americans.

00:40:01.420 --> 00:40:07.390
I will just put this
borrowed and modify lines

00:40:07.390 --> 00:40:10.960
from Martin Niemoller
up here for you to read.

00:40:10.960 --> 00:40:15.130
And then I will tell you what an
African American student wrote

00:40:15.130 --> 00:40:19.030
to me after he
listened to a talk

00:40:19.030 --> 00:40:22.540
that I gave at the University
of Maryland about my ordeal.

00:40:22.540 --> 00:40:28.720
He wrote in his email that I
cannot pretend to know what you

00:40:28.720 --> 00:40:31.190
feel or struggle with.

00:40:31.190 --> 00:40:33.380
I have been trained
my whole life

00:40:33.380 --> 00:40:38.090
knowing that situations such
as yours could happen to me.

00:40:40.660 --> 00:40:43.830
His great uncle was
wrongfully convicted

00:40:43.830 --> 00:40:48.760
of raping a white woman and
spent 25 years in prison,

00:40:48.760 --> 00:40:53.700
until it was shown that the
fingerprint in the evidence

00:40:53.700 --> 00:40:56.930
matched another man.

00:40:56.930 --> 00:41:04.150
So if race based persecution
and prosecution exists,

00:41:04.150 --> 00:41:07.960
for any ethnic
group of Americans,

00:41:07.960 --> 00:41:12.220
this practice infringe on
the constitutional rights

00:41:12.220 --> 00:41:13.850
of all Americans.

00:41:17.440 --> 00:41:24.280
So I want to call this
opinion of the Supreme Court

00:41:24.280 --> 00:41:28.210
associate justice Louis
Brandeis in his opinion

00:41:28.210 --> 00:41:33.730
in the wiretapping case of
Olmstead versus United States

00:41:33.730 --> 00:41:35.910
in 1928.

00:41:35.910 --> 00:41:39.810
He said that the greatest
dangers to liberty

00:41:39.810 --> 00:41:44.440
lurk in the insidious
encroachment by men of zeal,

00:41:44.440 --> 00:41:48.360
well-meaning but
without understanding.

00:41:48.360 --> 00:41:53.310
So the men of zeal
in my case obviously

00:41:53.310 --> 00:41:55.920
were without
understanding, right?

00:41:55.920 --> 00:41:58.340
Quite literally.

00:41:58.340 --> 00:42:01.520
But also that a man
of zeal can also

00:42:01.520 --> 00:42:06.710
be malicious, not well meaning.

00:42:06.710 --> 00:42:12.590
And I will say that persecution
or prosecution based on race

00:42:12.590 --> 00:42:17.270
and ethnic origin, ethnicity
and national origin,

00:42:17.270 --> 00:42:20.340
are definitely not well meaning.

00:42:20.340 --> 00:42:28.920
So that is why I ask this
question, why it matters?

00:42:28.920 --> 00:42:33.570
Because cases like
mine do not protect

00:42:33.570 --> 00:42:36.980
our intellectual properties.

00:42:36.980 --> 00:42:40.620
They threaten the
academic freedom.

00:42:40.620 --> 00:42:43.580
They hamper the US
research enterprise

00:42:43.580 --> 00:42:46.770
and economic well-being.

00:42:46.770 --> 00:42:49.850
And they undermine
people's confidence

00:42:49.850 --> 00:42:51.560
in America's legal system.

00:42:51.560 --> 00:42:53.420
And they terrorized
Chinese American

00:42:53.420 --> 00:42:55.670
in the scientific communities.

00:42:55.670 --> 00:43:00.680
And they endanger the liberty
that we cherish so much

00:43:00.680 --> 00:43:01.370
in this country.

00:43:04.130 --> 00:43:08.340
That is why I'm
telling my story.

00:43:08.340 --> 00:43:11.660
What happened to me
could happen to you,

00:43:11.660 --> 00:43:16.730
unless we all speak up as
one against racial profiling

00:43:16.730 --> 00:43:22.560
in government surveillance,
and any law enforcement.

00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:26.840
We have to work together
to stop this injustice

00:43:26.840 --> 00:43:29.812
of racial profiling.

00:43:29.812 --> 00:43:31.246
Thank you very much.

00:43:31.246 --> 00:43:32.680
[APPLAUSE]

00:43:37.146 --> 00:43:39.270
AUDIENCE: Coming from China,
and having experienced

00:43:39.270 --> 00:43:41.720
a cultural revolution,
you must have

00:43:41.720 --> 00:43:43.640
been thinking about
coming to the US

00:43:43.640 --> 00:43:48.980
to escape these kind
of accusations and loss

00:43:48.980 --> 00:43:51.512
of economic-- sorry,
academic freedom.

00:43:51.512 --> 00:43:52.970
But then you come
to US, experience

00:43:52.970 --> 00:43:56.590
the same, pretty much, same
things in essence again.

00:43:56.590 --> 00:44:00.990
So does that change
how you think

00:44:00.990 --> 00:44:05.760
about the essence of
the politics dynamics

00:44:05.760 --> 00:44:09.530
in China and the US and how
you think about the propaganda

00:44:09.530 --> 00:44:10.742
of governments?

00:44:14.469 --> 00:44:16.010
XIAOXING XI: You're
absolutely right.

00:44:16.010 --> 00:44:19.400
I mean, there is a
parallel in this.

00:44:19.400 --> 00:44:24.980
And I can even tell you a story
that illustrate this parallel.

00:44:24.980 --> 00:44:27.290
When I was in
elementary school--

00:44:27.290 --> 00:44:31.360
I forgot, maybe 12
years old or so--

00:44:31.360 --> 00:44:39.370
I was accused by my
teacher of saying

00:44:39.370 --> 00:44:41.410
Chairman Mao three years old.

00:44:41.410 --> 00:44:44.670
You know, at that time
everybody was forced to say,

00:44:44.670 --> 00:44:45.970
long live Chairman Mao.

00:44:45.970 --> 00:44:51.420
In Chinese that means
Chairman Mao, 10,000 years.

00:44:51.420 --> 00:44:57.330
And the Chinese character of
10,000, the scribble of it

00:44:57.330 --> 00:45:03.069
looks very similar to
the Arabic numeral three.

00:45:03.069 --> 00:45:05.610
So my teacher was saying I was
saying that Chairman Mao three

00:45:05.610 --> 00:45:06.990
years old.

00:45:06.990 --> 00:45:13.060
And the whole class you know,
condemn me for the class.

00:45:13.060 --> 00:45:14.770
So you are absolutely right.

00:45:14.770 --> 00:45:18.850
This kind of being
false accused,

00:45:18.850 --> 00:45:22.800
in a sense was not foreign
to us because I lived

00:45:22.800 --> 00:45:24.840
through cultural revolution.

00:45:24.840 --> 00:45:29.490
But absolutely, we were
not expecting it here

00:45:29.490 --> 00:45:31.050
in the United States.

00:45:31.050 --> 00:45:34.850
What I have to say is
that at least here there

00:45:34.850 --> 00:45:38.190
is this process,
a legal process,

00:45:38.190 --> 00:45:42.630
allowing me to defend
myself, to clear my name,

00:45:42.630 --> 00:45:46.980
if I have enough money
and if I have enough will.

00:45:46.980 --> 00:45:52.800
At least we have the system
that allows us to do this.

00:45:52.800 --> 00:45:58.320
But you are right, that
nobody should be naive,

00:45:58.320 --> 00:46:02.640
thinking that there is no
problem in this country.

00:46:02.640 --> 00:46:06.130
This country is a great country.

00:46:06.130 --> 00:46:08.430
We all love this country
that attracted people

00:46:08.430 --> 00:46:11.350
from all around the world
to come to this country.

00:46:11.350 --> 00:46:15.660
But this country also
have its problems.

00:46:15.660 --> 00:46:19.290
But this country has
a democratic process

00:46:19.290 --> 00:46:23.730
for all of us to get involved
so that we can change it

00:46:23.730 --> 00:46:24.850
for the better.

00:46:24.850 --> 00:46:30.010
That's why I'm talking,
telling people my story.

00:46:30.010 --> 00:46:35.450
I hope I can encourage
people to become more active,

00:46:35.450 --> 00:46:40.930
to, you know, take part
in the democratic process

00:46:40.930 --> 00:46:43.520
and speak up.

00:46:43.520 --> 00:46:48.860
Because we see racial
profiling happening and we

00:46:48.860 --> 00:46:56.600
have to unite to make our
voice against racial profiling

00:46:56.600 --> 00:47:00.580
loud and clear so
that politicians,

00:47:00.580 --> 00:47:05.840
the people with decision
power, will take that

00:47:05.840 --> 00:47:08.420
into their
consideration when they

00:47:08.420 --> 00:47:10.370
are making their decisions.

00:47:10.370 --> 00:47:16.850
So I hope that answer what
I'm thinking about this issue.

00:47:16.850 --> 00:47:18.500
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:47:18.500 --> 00:47:20.480
AUDIENCE: My question
was, you seemed

00:47:20.480 --> 00:47:22.640
to be at the peak
of your career,

00:47:22.640 --> 00:47:27.062
about to be named the chairman
of the physics department.

00:47:27.062 --> 00:47:28.520
Maybe you can tell
us a little more

00:47:28.520 --> 00:47:30.890
about what the
impact of all this

00:47:30.890 --> 00:47:33.640
has had on your
professional career.

00:47:33.640 --> 00:47:36.230
And also you mentioned
a lot about Joyce

00:47:36.230 --> 00:47:38.180
and the rest of your
family, maybe the impact

00:47:38.180 --> 00:47:40.240
it's had on them.

00:47:40.240 --> 00:47:41.840
XIAOXING XI: Well,
this obviously

00:47:41.840 --> 00:47:46.310
had a very significant
impact, the negative impact,

00:47:46.310 --> 00:47:47.930
on my career and my family.

00:47:53.830 --> 00:47:57.350
As you said, I was really
at the peak of my career.

00:47:57.350 --> 00:48:01.860
And I was working
24/7 on my research,

00:48:01.860 --> 00:48:04.820
or on my administrative
job, and so on and so forth.

00:48:04.820 --> 00:48:05.980
And then this happened.

00:48:05.980 --> 00:48:10.010
And now, not only that I could
not do my research and my work

00:48:10.010 --> 00:48:15.255
in that four months, but
the effect continues.

00:48:15.255 --> 00:48:16.800
The effect continues.

00:48:16.800 --> 00:48:20.400
And it's not going
go away very quickly.

00:48:20.400 --> 00:48:25.400
So my reputation is tainted now.

00:48:25.400 --> 00:48:32.890
And there are a lot of
opportunities that I would get

00:48:32.890 --> 00:48:35.920
otherwise, I cannot
get it anymore.

00:48:35.920 --> 00:48:38.810
And I was-- somebody was
asking me a similar question.

00:48:38.810 --> 00:48:42.880
I was telling people that there
are, for example, workshops

00:48:42.880 --> 00:48:45.820
of US-China
collaboration, cooperation

00:48:45.820 --> 00:48:46.910
on superconductivity.

00:48:46.910 --> 00:48:51.210
The organizers
would not invite me.

00:48:51.210 --> 00:48:54.200
And if I am thinking
about advancing

00:48:54.200 --> 00:48:58.690
in administrative roles,
well, I can forget about it.

00:48:58.690 --> 00:49:02.110
Who would give these
kind of opportunities

00:49:02.110 --> 00:49:05.710
to somebody who has
gone through like that,

00:49:05.710 --> 00:49:08.610
and they're charged
by the government?

00:49:08.610 --> 00:49:13.710
So my research group
is now a tiny portion

00:49:13.710 --> 00:49:18.830
of the group I had
before my arrest.

00:49:18.830 --> 00:49:26.380
And you know, I was concerned
that what I'm doing every day

00:49:26.380 --> 00:49:29.590
could be misconstrued
by the government

00:49:29.590 --> 00:49:34.550
for some evil purposes.

00:49:34.550 --> 00:49:40.060
And I am even scared when
I'm signing my names on forms

00:49:40.060 --> 00:49:42.770
that we need to do
for getting funding

00:49:42.770 --> 00:49:46.210
and manage my
research or products.

00:49:46.210 --> 00:49:51.940
So this kind of
effect on my career,

00:49:51.940 --> 00:49:53.710
it's not going to go away.

00:49:53.710 --> 00:49:59.390
And it's very, very negative.

00:49:59.390 --> 00:50:02.960
In terms of the family,
obviously we went through this.

00:50:02.960 --> 00:50:07.730
And my family, my wife, my
children, went through all this

00:50:07.730 --> 00:50:08.930
for no reason--

00:50:08.930 --> 00:50:09.710
for no reason.

00:50:09.710 --> 00:50:13.970
That was the toughest
thing for me,

00:50:13.970 --> 00:50:18.250
to see them suffer
because of me.

00:50:18.250 --> 00:50:23.750
And well, Joyce was
a chemistry major

00:50:23.750 --> 00:50:27.210
and now she's working in the
civil rights organization

00:50:27.210 --> 00:50:30.150
and trying to raise awareness
of people off the injustice

00:50:30.150 --> 00:50:32.680
that immigrants face.

00:50:32.680 --> 00:50:35.360
This changed her life.

00:50:35.360 --> 00:50:40.310
And our Sarah was trying
to go about her life

00:50:40.310 --> 00:50:41.510
like nothing happened.

00:50:41.510 --> 00:50:45.230
But we worry about
the long term effect.

00:50:45.230 --> 00:50:46.910
And we know that it hurt.

00:50:46.910 --> 00:50:48.560
You know, she was hurt.

00:50:48.560 --> 00:50:51.490
She was scared.

00:50:51.490 --> 00:50:54.970
AUDIENCE: Before your arrest
was, there any sign at all

00:50:54.970 --> 00:50:57.580
that something bad
could happen to you?

00:50:57.580 --> 00:51:00.940
Or was this just
pure surveillance

00:51:00.940 --> 00:51:05.110
that going in the background
that you never knew?

00:51:05.110 --> 00:51:07.210
XIAOXING XI: There was no sign.

00:51:07.210 --> 00:51:10.450
The very first thought
that I opened the door,

00:51:10.450 --> 00:51:12.720
see all these people there--

00:51:12.720 --> 00:51:13.290
what's that?

00:51:13.290 --> 00:51:14.540
This must be a mistake, right?

00:51:14.540 --> 00:51:16.770
They must mix up people's name?

00:51:16.770 --> 00:51:17.370
Why me?

00:51:17.370 --> 00:51:21.060
I have not done
anything remarkable.

00:51:21.060 --> 00:51:22.590
All these people--

00:51:22.590 --> 00:51:24.986
I was still thinking
a lot of things

00:51:24.986 --> 00:51:27.510
in the hat of a
department chair.

00:51:27.510 --> 00:51:29.310
I was thinking,
all these people.

00:51:29.310 --> 00:51:32.940
That must cost
government, the taxpayer,

00:51:32.940 --> 00:51:35.550
tons of money for them to
have all these people come

00:51:35.550 --> 00:51:36.990
to arrest me.

00:51:36.990 --> 00:51:39.490
For what?

00:51:39.490 --> 00:51:46.230
And so I was just like anybody.

00:51:46.230 --> 00:51:49.680
I read news about some Chinese
got arrested and charged

00:51:49.680 --> 00:51:50.850
and so on and so forth.

00:51:50.850 --> 00:51:55.470
I never thought that
it will happen to me.

00:51:55.470 --> 00:51:59.260
And I think a lot of people
are still thinking that way.

00:51:59.260 --> 00:52:00.720
So that's why I'm
telling people.

00:52:00.720 --> 00:52:03.900
I'm telling the details
about why they charged me,

00:52:03.900 --> 00:52:07.770
what are the exact things that
I did and so on and so forth,

00:52:07.770 --> 00:52:10.380
because I want
people to understand.

00:52:10.380 --> 00:52:14.850
You don't have to
do anything wrong.

00:52:14.850 --> 00:52:18.570
Just because maybe you
have a relative in China,

00:52:18.570 --> 00:52:21.000
you talk to them over the phone.

00:52:21.000 --> 00:52:25.500
Or maybe, you know,
you talk to somebody

00:52:25.500 --> 00:52:31.270
which they are monitoring,
that can get you in trouble.

00:52:31.270 --> 00:52:32.370
So it's very scary.

00:52:32.370 --> 00:52:34.650
I have to say that.

00:52:34.650 --> 00:52:37.230
But how do we change that?

00:52:37.230 --> 00:52:38.490
This is going to happen.

00:52:38.490 --> 00:52:41.850
The only way we can
change that is, we all

00:52:41.850 --> 00:52:46.680
unite together and speak up.

00:52:46.680 --> 00:52:53.340
And to make ourself a big
voice that the politicians have

00:52:53.340 --> 00:52:55.500
to worry about.

00:52:55.500 --> 00:52:59.410
They have to care about
our interests and so on.

00:52:59.410 --> 00:53:01.830
That's what the
democracy is all about.

00:53:01.830 --> 00:53:04.100
So that's why I'm talking.

00:53:04.100 --> 00:53:07.890
Every time I talk to people,
I reach a certain number

00:53:07.890 --> 00:53:09.670
of people.

00:53:09.670 --> 00:53:13.130
And I'm doing this
because I recognize,

00:53:13.130 --> 00:53:15.390
we just have to let
more and more and more

00:53:15.390 --> 00:53:20.020
people be aware
of such injustice.

00:53:20.020 --> 00:53:22.680
And everybody united
again, not just

00:53:22.680 --> 00:53:25.020
Chinese American,
Asian American,

00:53:25.020 --> 00:53:29.370
but African American,
Muslim American.

00:53:29.370 --> 00:53:33.390
All the people will suffer
from this kind of injustice.

00:53:33.390 --> 00:53:36.990
And uniting together,
and change it.

00:53:36.990 --> 00:53:42.130
And only then when
the law enforcement

00:53:42.130 --> 00:53:44.155
want to do something,
they have to be--

00:53:44.155 --> 00:53:47.050
at least there shouldn't
be a policy like,

00:53:47.050 --> 00:53:50.860
go after a particular
group of Americans.

00:53:50.860 --> 00:53:53.700
AUDIENCE: OK, well thank
you again Professor Xi.

00:53:53.700 --> 00:53:57.960
I really appreciate you
fighting against injustice,

00:53:57.960 --> 00:54:02.170
relating this to racial
injustice across America.

00:54:02.170 --> 00:54:04.560
Are there things that-- you
know, hearing your story

00:54:04.560 --> 00:54:05.060
is great.

00:54:05.060 --> 00:54:07.990
It makes us feel more angry
and wanting to do something.

00:54:07.990 --> 00:54:10.000
So how can we learn more?

00:54:10.000 --> 00:54:13.152
How can we find how
to help you and help

00:54:13.152 --> 00:54:14.110
